@startuml RegisterMember
title Activity Diagram: Register Member

' Description:
' This activity diagram describes the process of registering a new member in the library system.
' Steps:
' 1. Librarian initiates member registration.
' 2. Librarian enters member details (name, email, phone, password).
' 3. System validates the input fields for completeness and format.
' 4. If input is invalid, system shows validation errors and prompts re-entry.
' 5. System checks if the email is already registered in the system.
' 6. If email exists, system notifies the librarian of a duplicate account.
' 7. If email is new, system creates a new Member account with active status.
' 8. System assigns a unique member ID.
' 9. System sends a welcome/confirmation notification to the member's email.
' 10. Librarian receives confirmation of successful registration.
' 11. Activity ends.

|Librarian|
start
:Initiate Member Registration;
:Enter Member Details\n(name, email, phone, password);
|System|
:Validate Input Fields;
if (Input Valid?) then (yes)
  :Check for Duplicate Email;
  if (Email Already Exists?) then (yes)
    :Notify Duplicate Account;
    |Librarian|
    :Informed of Duplicate;
  else (no)
    :Create Member Account;
    :Assign Unique Member ID;
    :Set Account Status to Active;
    :Send Confirmation Email;
    |Librarian|
    :Confirm Successful Registration;
  endif
else (no)
  :Display Validation Errors;
  |Librarian|
  :Re-enter Member Details;
endif
stop
@enduml
